The paper discusses improvements to Tardos' collusion-resistant fingerprinting scheme, which is a topic in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the decoding algorithm for identifying potential colluders, which involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the potential application of the techniques to group testing methods, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV).
